    "about": "I am a software engineer, researcher, and designer. I hope to empower individuals to cultivate passion, insight, and joy; and to help others laugh and smile more.\n\nMy open-source software has reached millions of people, spanning work in distributed systems, programming languages, computer graphics, and interaction design. I enjoy working in small teams, sharing fresh engineering and design perspectives.\n\nHow I conceptualize my work: Computers influence our daily lives, augment how people think, and shape how we perceive each other and our visions for the world. They're pretty cool! And I think technology is ultimately in service to the wonderful ideas and places; beliefs, aspirations, and dreams of all the people who rely on it.\n\nI have a math degree and a CS graduate degree from Harvard. Not looking for jobs right now.",
